biogHist.abstract: The Ministerial Files and Associated Papers - Unregistered concern the portfolios of lands, national parks and wildlife, social welfare and international year of the disabled. They include the archival item, Aspect House file number AA568/1/143, which contains correspondence about the funding and closure of Aspect House.
biogHist.p:
Closed D30 years
D30 means this record is closed to the general public for 30 years from the date of the last entry in it. People wishing to access the record should contact the Minister (former Minister) who created them. In the event that they cannot be contacted, permission may be sought from the current leader of the parliamentary party which formed the government in which the Minister served. However, since these records are more than 30 years old, it is best to contact the Tasmanian Archive and Heritage Office first as the records may be open. Staff at the Office may also be able to assist you in finding other relevant records.
